<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
In Korea, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tanaka" authorityYear="1961" class="Hexanauplia" family="Clausidiidae" genus="Conchyliurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Conchyliurus quintus" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quintus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Conchyliurus quintus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed along the entire coast. It has a low host specificity, inhabiting 12 species of bivalves in Korea (
<bibRefCitation author="Kim, I-H" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Studies" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="187 - 192" refId="B29" refString="Kim, I-H, 2004. Copepods associated with bivalves in Korea and their distribution. Zoological Studies 43 (2): 187 - 192" title="Copepods associated with bivalves in Korea and their distribution." volume="43" year="2004">Kim 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
